        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/19345",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jeffrey",
                        "name": "jeffrey",
                        "displayName": "Jeffrey Sambells",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "After much testing I've determined this is the result of the require_once structure in the various files. It seems that if you don't require the object in the correct order it creates a \"loop\" where the require structure dies and the object is never really instantiated. The error actually occurs when you simply require the file! If you haven't loaded any other PDF stuff, just do this:\n\nrequire 'Zend\/Pdf\/Resource\/Image.php';\n\nand you'll get the error. This happens because the require line do this:\n\n\nZend\/Pdf\/Resource\/Image.php\nrequires -> \nZend\/Pdf\/Element\/Object.php\nrequires -> \nZend\/Pdf\/ElementFactory.php\nrequires -> \nZend\/Pdf\/Element\/Reference.php\nrequires -> \n\/Zend\/Pdf\/Element\/Reference\/Context.php\nrequires -> \nZend\/Pdf\/StringParser.php\nrequires -> \nZend\/Pdf\/Element\/Object\/Stream.php\nrequires -> \nZend\/Pdf\/Element\/Stream.php\nrequires -> \nZend\/Pdf.php\nrequires -> \nZend\/Pdf\/Resource\/Image\/Jpeg.php\nrequires -> \nZend\/Pdf\/Resource\/Image.php \n\nLOOP!!!\n\nThe last require doesn't actually happen since it already occurred (once) above but that means PHP then tries to parse Zend_Pdf_Resource_Image_Jpeg BEFORE Zend_Pdf_Resource_Image has been parsed.\n\nThe same applies to Tiff and such if you start requiring different files.\n\n\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jeffrey",
                        "name": "jeffrey",
                        "displayName": "Jeffrey Sambells",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-02-21T12:46:58.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-02-21T12:46:58.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/20572",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=wil",
                        "name": "wil",
                        "displayName": "Wil Sinclair",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Please evaluate and categorize as necessary.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=wil",
                        "name": "wil",
                        "displayName": "Wil Sinclair",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-03-31T16:12:00.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-03-31T16:12:00.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23102",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=alexander",
                        "name": "alexander",
                        "displayName": "Alexander Veremyev",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Zend_Pdf component objects are not intended to be used one by one.\n\nIn some places it's only \"declaration\", that this class needs som other(s). And it sometimes makes loops.\n\nActual require_once (and file parcing) order is defined by require_once tree (graph) starting from Zend_Pdf.\n\nSo you should always use:\n{code}\n<?php\nrequire_once 'Zend\/Pdf.php';\n...\n{code}\nto work with Zend_Pdf component.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=alexander",
                        "name": "alexander",
                        "displayName": "Alexander Veremyev",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-07-26T04:57:11.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-07-26T04:57:11.000+0000"
